leaving it all to the grandkids.

04:34.800 --> 04:35.516
What do you mean?

04:35.600 --> 04:38.160
Like, splitting everything
between the grandkids.

04:39.440 --> 04:41.271
What? Steve has three kids.

04:41.560 --> 04:43.915
He's already rich. We only have one.
How's that fair?

04:44.560 --> 04:45.754
It's not up to me.

04:46.280 --> 04:49.511
They also talked about just giving it all
to charity, so, who knows?

04:49.800 --> 04:50.800
Seriously?

04:51.960 --> 04:52.960
That's absurd.

04:54.640 --> 04:55.709
Seriously, that's mean.

04:56.120 --> 04:58.793
You work for a nonprofit,
and you think that's absurd?

04:59.080 --> 05:01.674
Right, I work for a nonprofit.
You work for the government.

05:02.640 --> 05:03.640
We need the money.

05:04.280 --> 05:07.158
Look, I'm gonna be so distraught
when my parents die,

05:07.320 --> 05:09.151
I'm not gonna give a fuck about the money.

05:09.840 --> 05:10.840
Really?

05:12.160 --> 05:13.160
Not at all?

05:15.160 --> 05:16.160
Think you will.

05:17.480 --> 05:18.480
What about your dad?

05:19.080 --> 05:20.354
You have money coming to you.

05:20.440 --> 05:22.317
Oh, he's an academic. I mean...

05:23.840 --> 05:25.432
two hundred thousand, maybe.

05:25.520 --> 05:27.556
Well, that'll help pay for Troy's college.

05:28.720 --> 05:30.600
Is that why you're worrying about money?

05:32.560 --> 05:33.560
We'll be fine.

05:35.160 --> 05:36.275
We'll figure it out.

05:41.960 --> 05:44.633
We didn't work this hard
to end up dying in a flophouse, you know?

05:44.720 --> 05:46.080
All right, you're freaking me out.

05:47.360 --> 05:49.040
I just feel like
we're running out of time.

05:51.360 --> 05:52.873
It's like there's no more potential.

05:53.840 --> 05:54.840
This is it.

05:56.520 --> 05:57.520
We've plateaued.

05:58.640 --> 06:00.160
It's not like there's gonna be some...

06:01.160 --> 06:04.789
windfall that, you know,
suddenly changes our situation.

06:04.880 --> 06:05.880
I mean...

06:06.920 --> 06:08.956
We're not poor, Brad.
I kn...

06:11.200 --> 06:12.679
In some circles, yeah.

06:13.120 --> 06:15.554
Oh, what circles? The one percent?

06:19.280 --> 06:20.508
We have a great life.

06:22.040 --> 06:23.040
Go to sleep.

06:27.280 --> 06:28.856
Do you think you should
talk to your parents?

06:28.880 --> 06:30.000
Then we'll get some clarity.

06:32.640 --> 06:34.073
You and I are done.
I love you.

06:34.160 --> 06:35.160
Please shut up.

07:06.680 --> 07:07.680
Troy?

07:10.040 --> 07:11.520
Troy, are you up?

