Oh, yes. Hello.

07:18.280 --> 07:19.280
What is your name?

07:19.800 --> 07:20.949
I know your name.

07:27.880 --> 07:28.880
You have ten minutes.

07:29.040 --> 07:31.759
Uh, yeah, I'm ready.
I just got to put on my clothes.

07:35.680 --> 07:36.795
Can you give me a second?

07:37.960 --> 07:38.870
Yeah.

07:38.960 --> 07:41.190
You have, like, the body of a man now.

07:42.000 --> 07:44.230
Hey, Dad, can you not be weird?
'Cause I'm stressed.

07:45.160 --> 07:46.160
Okay.

07:46.800 --> 07:47.800
Can you close my door?

07:48.560 --> 07:49.560
Yeah.

07:49.920 --> 07:51.120
Can you close the door?

07:51.560 --> 07:52.560
Yeah.

07:57.480 --> 07:59.675
Yeah, it looks good.
Did you bring a jacket?

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
- Yeah.
- Okay. It's gonna get cold.

08:03.040 --> 08:03.677
- Yeah.
- Oh,

08:03.760 --> 08:05.136
I think you guys are gonna like this.

08:05.160 --> 08:06.880
Yeah, I think
it'll be good, I guess.

08:08.480 --> 08:09.840
On the ride to the airport,

08:10.120 --> 08:12.156
I kept thinking
about what Chris Kanew said.

08:14.400 --> 08:16.160
So, wait a minute,
you're going into banking?

08:16.640 --> 08:19.916
Look, Brad, I honestly think
I can do so much more good

08:20.000 --> 08:22.195
by making a lot of money
and then giving it away,

08:22.280 --> 08:24.475
instead of spending all my time
asking other people

08:24.560 --> 08:25.959
for their money to give away.

08:27.360 --> 08:28.475
You know what I mean?

08:32.320 --> 08:33.655
You have
all the hotel information, right?

08:33.679 --> 08:34.953
Yeah, Mom. It's on my phone.

08:35.039 --> 08:36.336
Would you forward it to your dad?

08:36.360 --> 08:38.760
I don't think he has any sense
of the schedule. Do you, Brad?

08:39.760 --> 08:42.159
I don't think he has any idea,
so, it's really on you, honey.

08:42.360 --> 08:42.996
Okay.

08:43.080 --> 08:45.992
There are moments you realize
your entire life's work is absurd

08:47.080 --> 08:48.456
and you have nothing to show for it.

08:48.480 --> 08:50.536
...- the deputies of Kim Jong-il.
- Yeah.

08:52.200 --> 08:54.816
Or maybe it was Kim Jong-un.
Was it Kim Jong-un or Kim Jong-il?

08:54.840 --> 08:56.717
- Was it the father?
- It was ll.

08:57.040 --> 08:58.080
That's the father.

08:58.680 --> 09:00.033
Some guys have empires.

09:01.200 --> 09:02.200
What do I have?

09:03.280 --> 09:04.554
I live in Sacramento,

09:04.920 --> 09:07.480
a secondary market
surrounded by mediocrities

09:07.560 --> 09:08.560
and beta males.

09:08.880 --> 09:10.108
...this piece on NPR.

09:10.200 --> 09:13.033
It was an interview. It was Terry Gross
with All Things Considered.

09:13.720 --> 09:16.216
But the guy... you were telling
about the guy in the prison before,

09:16.240 --> 09:17.856
- the vegetarian guy, right?
- Oh, yeah.

09:17.880 --> 09:19.757
In this... It's a private prison
in Georgia.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.514
And they have meat in every dish.

09:22.880 --> 09:24.736
This guy just said,
"I'm gonna stop eating meat."

09:24.760 --> 09:27.480
So, they got him tied down.
They're force-feeding him through a tube.

09:27.960 --> 09:30.952
And he just keeps saying,
"Vegetables. Vegetarian. Fruit."

09:34.640 --> 09:36.320
This is not where I thought I'd be.

09:39.800 --> 09:41.233
It's not the life I imagined.

09:43.600 --> 09:45.320
Oh, honey,
this is gonna be so cool.

09:46.080 --> 09:47.080
This is great.

09:48.600 --> 09:51.720
Mom, I think I'm just gonna take
Old River Road, connect to the freeway.

09:52.440 --> 09:53.936
For your safety and security...

09:53.960 --> 09:54.960
This good?

09:55.120 --> 09:56.120
Yeah.

10:08.120 --> 10:09.256
Call me all the time.

10:09.280 --> 10:11.430
I want to know everything.
This is so exciting.

10:11.520 --> 10:12.696
- Yeah, thanks, Mom.
- I love you.

10:12.720 --> 10:13.835
All right. Should be good.

10:14.480 --> 10:15.833
I can't believe this.

10:15.920 --> 10:17.114
This is crazy.
I know.

10:17.200 --> 10:18.416
It just feels like a big moment.

10:18.440 --> 10:21.240
I'm so jealous. I can't believe
I have to go to this stupid conference.

10:21.400 --> 10:22.616
Okay, flight info's all on your phone,

10:22.640 --> 10:24.336
and the hotels, it's all on there, okay?
Great, okay.

10:24.360 --> 10:26.136
- All right, be happy. Be present.
- Love you.

10:26.160 --> 10:26.956
All right.
I love you.

10:27.040 --> 10:28.416
- Love you, honey.
- Okay.

10:28.440 --> 10:29.793
Oh, take lots of pictures!

10:32.200 --> 10:32.950
Love you!

10:33.040 --> 10:34.040
Love you!

10:34.960 --> 10:36.480
Attention, all departing passengers...

10:41.640 --> 10:42.959
Economy entrance is that line.

10:43.400 --> 10:45.789
But, uh, I have a, uh, Silver Flyer card.

10:46.400 --> 10:47.674
It's Gold and Platinum only.

10:54.320 --> 10:55.320
Next, please.

10:57.320 --> 10:58.320
Enjoy your flight.

11:36.400 --> 11:37.480
You know what I'm thinking?

11:37.720 --> 11:38.720
Hmm?

11:38.880 --> 11:39.915
Let's try for an upgrade.

11:41.080 --> 11:42.080
What do you mean?

11:43.200 --> 11:44.440
Going off to find your college.

11:46.040 --> 11:48.801
And I don't know when you and I
