Okay.
All right.

12:05.400 --> 12:08.790
Oh! Good news.
There are two seats available in business.

12:08.880 --> 12:09.880
Oh!

12:11.480 --> 12:13.240
Can I see
your tickets, please?

12:13.320 --> 12:14.320
Awesome.

12:14.560 --> 12:16.198
Yeah.
Thank you.

12:16.360 --> 12:18.396
Yeah. I was hoping to put it on my miles.

12:18.920 --> 12:20.200
I got a bunch of miles, I think.

12:20.400 --> 12:22.709
Unfortunately, no, not with this flight,
you can't.

12:23.960 --> 12:26.679
So...
cost to upgrade to business

12:26.760 --> 12:29.194
would be $821 per ticket.
Mm.

12:29.920 --> 12:33.230
So, the total would be $1,642.

12:34.280 --> 12:37.750
Sixteen hundred dollars?
That's... for a domestic flight?

12:37.840 --> 12:39.068
Yes, $1,642.

12:40.000 --> 12:42.040
Would you like to go ahead
and purchase the tickets?

12:42.440 --> 12:43.509
I...

12:44.600 --> 12:45.600
I'm gonna go for it.

12:46.280 --> 12:48.748
Go for it. I can put it on my Amex.
Actually... Sorry, no.

12:49.920 --> 12:51.148
Put it on my MasterCard.

12:51.880 --> 12:54.599
Thanks.
Gonna put it on the Amex. Just...

12:57.360 --> 12:58.031
Okay.

12:58.120 --> 13:00.111
Sorry.
Great. Let me just run that.

13:02.280 --> 13:05.670
Yeah, it's a... once-in-a-lifetime thing.

13:06.160 --> 13:08.230
Mm-hmm. Mr. Sloan, actually...
Yeah?

13:08.320 --> 13:10.675
...unfortunately, we can't upgrade you.

13:10.800 --> 13:12.279
I'm sorry.
What? Why not?

13:12.760 --> 13:15.672
Seems as though you bought those tickets
on a discounted website,

13:15.760 --> 13:18.752
and with that type of ticket,
we can't do the upgrade.

13:20.640 --> 13:21.356
Okay.

13:21.440 --> 13:24.796
But... not even if I pay you $1,600?

13:24.880 --> 13:27.599
There's actually no amount of money
you can pay to get an upgrade.

13:28.080 --> 13:29.080
I'm so sorry.

13:29.520 --> 13:30.520
Anything else?

13:30.680 --> 13:33.035
Um... no.

13:33.120 --> 13:35.270
It's not a big deal, anyway.

13:36.160 --> 13:36.751
Okay.

13:36.840 --> 13:38.478
And what if I'm a Silver Flyer member?

13:39.080 --> 13:40.080
I'm sorry.

13:40.120 --> 13:41.120
Next?
Okay.

13:41.840 --> 13:42.976
Right on the beach.

13:43.000 --> 13:44.000
Really?

13:44.520 --> 13:45.536
- Champagne?
- That sounds like...

13:45.560 --> 13:46.576
- Oh!
- There you are.

13:46.600 --> 13:47.396
Thanks.
Thank you.

13:47.480 --> 13:48.993
Yes. Enjoy your flight.

14:07.920 --> 14:09.360
Sorry I couldn't get us the upgrade.

14:10.600 --> 14:11.669
It's not a big deal.

14:12.320 --> 14:14.311
Silver Flyer card.

14:15.680 --> 14:16.556
Means nothing.

14:16.640 --> 14:17.709
Gets you nothing at all.

14:18.240 --> 14:19.240
Well, then get rid of it.

14:19.960 --> 14:21.313
Yeah, I'm gonna. I'm tossing it.

14:24.280 --> 14:25.395
Should I? I should, right?

14:25.800 --> 14:26.800
Mm-hmm.

14:27.400 --> 14:28.400
Stupid...

14:34.480 --> 14:35.913
I'll keep it for now.

14:49.080 --> 14:50.416
I couldn't help but wonder:

14:50.440 --> 14:52.954
When was the last time
Craig Fisher flew economy?

14:54.560 --> 14:55.629
Probably not in decades.

14:55.720 --> 14:56.720
Mr. Fisher?

14:57.000 --> 14:58.194
Can I offer you a warm towel?

14:59.400 --> 15:00.799
A warm towel.

15:00.920 --> 15:02.069
Yes, thank you.

15:06.840 --> 15:08.296
What are you two doing?

15:08.320 --> 15:10.754
And now Jason Hatfield
has his own private plane.

15:11.760 --> 15:13.318
Never has to fly commercial at all.

15:20.440 --> 15:22.590
Nick Pascale probably flies private, too.

15:25.360 --> 15:26.475
Thank you so much.

15:28.280 --> 15:30.714
Must be nice to always have
the seas part for you.

15:33.440 --> 15:34.509
Nothing's out of reach.

15:35.040 --> 15:36.200
Can I have this one?

15:37.280 --> 15:38.395
- Okay.
- Yeah? Oh.

15:38.720 --> 15:39.840
Everything an option.

15:41.760 --> 15:42.760
Must be like a drug.

15:43.960 --> 15:46.633
Always feeling important and special.

15:48.000 --> 15:49.000
Better than.

15:49.280 --> 15:51.400
And all the adventures.

15:52.440 --> 15:53.919
The exotic destinations.

15:54.440 --> 15:55.440
Au revoir!

16:00.720 --> 16:02.560
For them,
the world isn't a battlefield.

16:04.280 --> 16:05.280
It's a playground.

16:07.600 --> 16:08.600
A dream.

16:14.560 --> 16:17.154
It's heaven, manifested.

16:20.320 --> 16:22.360
Dad, can I get some Pringles?
They're seven dollars.

16:26.200 --> 16:27.520
- Yeah.
- I need your credit card.

16:28.120 --> 16:30.429
There are 45 minutes left on the flight.

16:30.520 --> 16:33.159
Keep your seat belt fastened.
Enjoy the rest of the flight.

16:42.120 --> 16:44.270
Eventually,
my mind drifted back to college.

16:47.840 --> 16:50.400
Back then, I was in love with the world

16:50.880 --> 16:52.359
and the world was in love with me.

16:58.840 --> 17:00.600
When did we fall out of love
with each other?

17:08.880 --> 17:09.920
Where did it all go wrong?

17:16.440 --> 17:17.792
My thoughts turned to Melanie.

17:18.920 --> 17:19.715
It's unbelievable.

17:19.800 --> 17:20.800
It's fucked up.

17:21.160 --> 17:23.627
They've got kids...
little elementary school kids...

17:23.880 --> 17:26.553
doing these mass-shooting drills
in their schools,

17:26.640 --> 17:28.536
because everybody has to have a gun,
because that's the answer...

17:28.560 --> 17:31.199
I love Melanie's idealism,
but maybe that idealism

17:31.320 --> 17:32.878
prevented me from ever selling out.

17:35.680 --> 17:38.035
Jason Hatfield married a woman
who had money of her own.

17:39.040 --> 17:42.635
She introduced him to rich clients,
gave him entrÃ©e and status.

17:44.720 --> 17:46.392
Diane Fisher's famous in her own right.

17:47.280 --> 17:48.840
She and Craig competed with each other,

17:49.920 --> 17:51.512
pushing each other to succeed.

17:53.280 --> 17:54.030
Here.
Oh.

17:54.120 --> 17:55.120
But Melanie...

17:55.520 --> 17:57.272
she's so easily satisfied.

17:57.360 --> 17:58.360
It's good.

17:58.760 --> 18:00.159
Seriously?
Yeah!

18:00.640 --> 18:02.392
Honestly?
Yeah, I always love your sauces.

18:03.600 --> 18:05.296
Maybe her contentment
undermined my ambition.

18:05.320 --> 18:06.320
Okay.

18:14.920 --> 18:16.148
Hey. Hi, honey.

18:16.280 --> 18:17.190
Hey, you in Boston?

18:17.280 --> 18:18.280
Yep. We made it.

18:18.920 --> 18:20.360
Yeah, we're on our way to the hotel.

18:20.440 --> 18:21.920
Oh, good. How's Troy doing?

18:22.320 --> 18:23.435
He's good.
Good.

18:24.400 --> 18:26.834
Yeah. He's, uh, drinking in Boston.

18:34.400 --> 18:37.392
And I'll tell you something:
I know exactly what the...

18:43.640 --> 18:45.517
I can't blame Melanie
for my decisions,

18:45.840 --> 18:46.840
or anyone else.

18:50.680 --> 18:51.680
It's my fault.

18:52.800 --> 18:53.800
Dad.

18:54.640 --> 18:57.473
You want to get some food? All I've eaten
today is the can of Pringles.

18:59.600 --> 19:01.397
Yeah. Let's do it. I'm hungry, too.

19:02.160 --> 19:03.718
Yeah. Let's get some food.

19:15.680 --> 19:19.229
And then, uh, Thursday, rent a car
and drive to Amherst and then Williams.

19:19.320 --> 19:21.959
You know,
these are competitive schools, Troy.

19:22.960 --> 19:25.315
Just... just try not to put
too much pressure on yourself.

19:25.400 --> 19:26.400
You know what I mean?

19:26.480 --> 19:28.391
Don't get caught up
in the game, all the brands.

19:29.200 --> 19:31.509
You know, "Williams,"
"Harvard," all of it.

19:32.520 --> 19:33.999
Just... It all works out.

19:34.360 --> 19:35.976
In the end, you end up at the right place.

19:36.000 --> 19:37.096
Mm, yeah, I'm not really worried.

19:37.120 --> 19:38.120
Okay.

19:38.960 --> 19:42.191
You know, when I was your age,
I was so freaked out about college.

19:42.760 --> 19:43.760
I wanted to go to Yale.

